      "writtenOn": "2019-11-08T13:57:15Z",
      "side": 1,
      "message": "I\u0027d probably rather add a new method that returns the frame count than access the SkAndroidCodec directly.\n\nWhat do clients want to do with the frame count, though? It seems funny to expose it, since we don\u0027t currently offer an API to choose which frame you want to decode.\n\nFWIW, the reason I did *not* add such an API is that I wasn\u0027t planning to use it on Android. It allows skipping ahead to \"catch up\", but I\u0027ve found that to be a bad user experience. That said, it also allows arbitrary seeking, which some clients request.",
      "range": {
        "startLine": 851,
        "startChar": 0,
        "endLine": 853,
        "endChar": 11
      },
      "revId": "7108a64b74a5f62587aa8eca0358dd6f2a04c848",
      "serverId": "5086850b-e599-37d2-8ec8-ff16aeccbf02",
      "unresolved": true
    },
    {
      "key": {
        "uuid": "5a4d0b4b_883aa0a0",
        "filename": "modules/canvaskit/canvaskit_bindings.cpp",
        "patchSetId": 3
      },
      "lineNbr": 853,
      "author": {
        "id": 5395
      },
      "writtenOn": "2019-11-08T14:36:50Z",
      "side": 1,
      "message": "Flutter\u0027s animated image API [1] has getters for both repetition count and frames, but only exposes a frame iterator. \n\nIn C++ land, under the hood, they take encoded bytes, plug them into SkCodec and then ask SkCodec how many frames the image has to see if they need to wrap it as a SingleFrameImage or a MultiFrameImage before passing it off to the client. For flutter-web, they want to do the same trick.\n\nI added the new methods to SkAnimatedImage, WDYT?\n\n[1] https://api.flutter.dev/flutter/dart-ui/Codec-class.html",
      "parentUuid": "38913d89_23408d2f",
      "range": {
        "startLine": 851,
        "startChar": 0,
        "endLine": 853,
        "endChar": 11
      },
      "revId": "7108a64b74a5f62587aa8eca0358dd6f2a04c848",
      "serverId": "5086850b-e599-37d2-8ec8-ff16aeccbf02",
      "unresolved": true
    },
